      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like the school's side is being framed as this big thing for \"progress\" and being \"empathetic.\" it makes the parents who are worried sound like they're just stuck in the past or something. isnt there a valid way to look at it from the parents maybe? like, whats their actual argument beyond just \"tradition\"?",
